An application for conversion may only be approved if it is found that:
The converting mutual association has met the requirements of Title 6 of this article;
The converting mutual association will qualify for share insurance by the Credit Union Insurance Corporation or the National Credit Union Administration Share Program;
The converting mutual association has credited to the reserve fund 6 percent of its risk assets; and
The public interest will be promoted by allowing the mutual association to convert to a credit union.
